---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - PA.VE.SA. srl"
  description="Privacy policy and personal data processing of PA.VE.SA. srl in compliance with GDPR"
  lang="en"
>
  <!-- Privacy Content -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-white dark:bg-[#121212] transition-colors">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h1 class="heading-border text-center text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold dark:text-gray-100">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
        </div>
        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy describes how the website <strong>www.pavesasrl.it</strong> manages
          the personal data of users who visit it, in compliance with EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR).
        </p>

        <h3>Data Controller</h3>

        <p>
          The Data Controller is:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>PA.VE.SA. srl</strong></li>
          <li>Registered office: Via Germania, 4 - 86034 Guglionesi (CB), Italy</li>
          <li>Administrative office: Contrada piane di Larino, 90 - 86035 Larino (CB), Italy</li>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:info@pavesasrl.it">info@pavesasrl.it</a></li>
          <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+390875808184">0875808184</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Types of Data Collected</h3>

        <p>
          The website collects personal data voluntarily provided by users through:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact forms</strong> - name, email, phone, message</li>
          <li><strong>Technical cookies</strong> - browsing data necessary for the website to function</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> - Google Analytics for aggregated anonymous statistics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Purpose of Processing</h3>

        <p>Personal data is processed for the following purposes:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Response to information requests</strong> - managing communications sent through contact forms</li>
          <li><strong>Service improvement</strong> - statistical analysis on navigation to optimize user experience</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligations</strong> - fiscal, accounting and legal compliance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Legal Basis of Processing</h3>

        <p>The processing of personal data is based on:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consent of the data subject</strong> (art. 6, par. 1, lett. a GDPR) - for sending commercial communications</li>
          <li><strong>Performance of a contract</strong> (art. 6, par. 1, lett. b GDPR) - for managing requests and quotes</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> (art. 6, par. 1, lett. f GDPR) - for statistical analysis and website security</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Methods of Processing</h3>

        <p>
          Personal data is processed using electronic and manual tools, adopting appropriate security
          measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, modification or destruction.
        </p>

        <p>Data processing is carried out by:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Authorized personnel of the Data Controller</li>
          <li>Designated data processors (e.g. hosting providers, email services)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Data Retention</h3>

        <p>Personal data is retained for the time strictly necessary for the purposes for which it was collected:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact requests</strong> - up to 24 months from receipt</li>
          <li><strong>Contractual data</strong> - for the entire duration of the relationship and subsequently for legal obligations (10 years)</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> - up to 26 months</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Communication and Disclosure of Data</h3>

        <p>
          Personal data is not publicly disclosed. It may be communicated to:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>Subjects providing IT system management services (hosting, maintenance)</li>
          <li>Professionals and consultants (accountants, lawyers)</li>
          <li>Public authorities and supervisory bodies, upon request</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Rights of the Data Subject</h3>

        <p>
          Users have the right, at any time, to exercise the following rights provided by the GDPR:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> (art. 15) - obtain confirmation of the existence of their data and receive a copy</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> (art. 16) - request the correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> (art. 17) - obtain the deletion of data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> (art. 18) - request the restriction of processing</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> (art. 20) - receive data in structured format and transmit it to another controller</li>
          <li><strong>Objection</strong> (art. 21) - object to processing for legitimate reasons</li>
          <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong> - withdraw consent at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          To exercise these rights, users can send a request to:
          <a href="mailto:info@pavesasrl.it">info@pavesasrl.it</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          Users also have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent supervisory authority
          (<a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Italian Data Protection Authority</a>).
        </p>

        <h3>Cookie Policy & Preferences Management</h3>

        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that websites visited by users send to their terminals, where they are stored to be retransmitted to the same sites on subsequent visits.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          This website uses the following types of cookies:
        </p>

        <ul class="mb-6">
          <li><strong>Technical / Necessary Cookies:</strong> These are essential to allow navigation on the site and use its features (for example, to store your cookie consent preferences). Without these cookies, the site could not function properly.</li>
          <li><strong>Statistical / Analytical Cookies:</strong> We use Google Analytics to collect information in anonymous and aggregated form on the number of users and how they visit the site (most viewed pages, time spent, etc.) to improve its performance. They are loaded only with your explicit consent.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-3 dark:text-gray-100">Cookies Used on This Website</h4>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-lg">
          <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-800 text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Cookie Name</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Provider / Third Party</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Purpose</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Expiration</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Type</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-[#121212]">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">pavesa-cookie-consent</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">First Party (pavesasrl.it)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Stores the user's cookie consent status.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">1 year</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">Technical (Necessary)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">_ga</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Third Party (Google Analytics)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Used to distinguish unique users to generate statistical data.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">2 years</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs font-bold text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400">Statistical (Analytics)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">_ga_*</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Third Party (Google Analytics)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Used to store and maintain session state.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">2 years</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs font-bold text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400">Statistical (Analytics)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-3 dark:text-gray-100">Managing and Revoking Consent</h4>
        <p>
          You can modify or revoke your consent at any time by clicking the button below.
        </p>
        
        <div class="my-6">
          <button
            id="btn-reopen-cookie-preferences"
            class="px-6 py-3 font-bold text-black bg-pavesa-yellow rounded-md hover:bg-pavesa-yellow-hover hover:scale-105 transition-all transform shadow-sm cursor-pointer inline-flex items-center space-x-2"
          >
            <i class="fas fa-cog"></i>
            <span>Customize Cookie Preferences</span>
          </button>
        </div>

        <script>
          function initReopenButton() {
            const btn = document.getElementById('btn-reopen-cookie-preferences');
            if (btn) {
              btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('open-cookie-preferences'));
              });
            }
          }
          // Support standard load and view transitions
          document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initReopenButton);
          document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initReopenButton);
        </script>

        <h3>Changes to the Privacy Policy</h3>

        <p>
          The Data Controller reserves the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time.
          Changes will be published on this page with indication of the date of last update.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-pavesa-gray mt-8">
          <strong>Last update:</strong> January 13, 2026
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: var(--pavesa-dark);
  }

  :global(.dark) .prose {
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    color: var(--pavesa-dark);
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--pavesa-yellow);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  :global(.dark) .prose h2 {
    color: #f3f4f6;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    color: var(--pavesa-dark);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  :global(.dark) .prose h3 {
    color: #f3f4f6;
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .prose ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose ul li::before {
    content: "▸";
    color: var(--pavesa-yellow);
    font-weight: bold;
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--pavesa-dark);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  :global(.dark) .prose strong {
    color: #f3f4f6;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--pavesa-yellow);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
